{{Infobox settlement |official_name = Rijeka Crnojevića |native_name = Ријека Црнојевића |other_name = |settlement_type = Town |image_skyline =Rijeka Crnojevića.jpg |imagesize = |image_caption =The old [[Rijeka Crnojevića bridge]] |image_flag = |flag_size = |image_seal = |seal_size = |nickname = |motto = |image_map = |mapsize = |map_caption = |pushpin_map =Montenegro |pushpin_label_position =bottom |pushpin_mapsize= |pushpin_map_caption = |coordinates = {{coord|42|21|N|19|2|E|display=inline}} |subdivision_type = Country |subdivision_name ={{flag|Montenegro}} |subdivision_type1 = [[Municipalities of Montenegro|Municipality]] |subdivision_type2 = |subdivision_type3 = |subdivision_name1 = [[Cetinje Municipality|Cetinje]] |subdivision_name2 = |subdivision_name3 = |established_title = |established_date = |government_footnotes = |government_type = |leader_title = |leader_name = |unit_pref =Imperial |area_footnotes = |area_magnitude = |area_total_km2 = |area_land_km2 = |elevation_footnotes = |elevation_m = |elevation_ft = |population_total =175 |population_as_of =2011 |population_footnotes = |population_density_km2 = |population_note = |postal_code_type = |postal_code = |area_code = |website = |footnotes = |timezone =[[Central European Time|CET]] |utc_offset = +1 |timezone_DST = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]] |utc_offset_DST = +2 |blank_name = |blank_info = }} '''Rijeka Crnojevića''' ([[Cyrillic alphabet|Montenegrin Cyrillic]]: Ријека Црнојевића), meaning the river of [[House of Crnojević|Crnojević]], is a town in [[Montenegro]] besides the eponymous river, near the coast of [[Skadar lake]].
==History==
The [[Ottoman Empire|Ottomans]] captured [[Žabljak Crnojevića]] in 1478 after they defeated main army of [[Ivan Crnojević]] in late 1477 or early 1478.<ref>{{Citation|last=Fine|first=John Van Antwerp|title=The Late Medieval Balkans: A Critical Survey from the Late Twelfth Century to the Ottoman Conquest|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LvVbRrH1QBgC&pg=PA600 |year=1994|publisher=University of Michigan Press|isbn=978-0-472-08260-5|page=600 |quote=The second Ottoman wave of 1477 overran much of Zeta, taking Žabljak and the late in 1477 or early 1478 meeting and defeating John Crnojevićs main army.}}</ref> Ivan moved his seat to Obod (fortified by him in 1475<ref name="Samardžić1892">{{cite book|author=Radovan Samardžić|title=Istorija srpskog naroda: Doba borbi za očuvanje i obnovu države 1371-1537|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KXNpAAAAMAAJ|accessdate=24 April 2013|year=1892|publisher=Srpska knjiiževna zadruga|page=419|quote=После повлачења из Жабљака, Иван Црнојевић је боравио у Ободу (Ријека Црнојевића), који је утврдио око 1475. године. }}</ref>) which was soon renamed to Rijeka Crnojevića, and became the new capital of Montenegro.<ref name="Немировски1996">{{cite book|author=Евгениј Љвович Немировски|title=Почеци штампарства у Црној Гори, 1492-1496|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cV4VAQAAIAAJ|accessdate=24 April 2013|year=1996|publisher=ЦНБ "Ђурђе Црнојевић"|page=99|quote=Како је Жабљак био разрушен, Иван Црнојевић је пренио престоницу на Обод или Ријеку, утврђено мјесто код извора ријеке, која је касније добила назив Ријека Црнојевића. }}</ref>
Rijeka Crnojevića was the historical seat of [[Riječka nahija]], one of the four territorial units of [[Old Montenegro]].
