'''Anthony Howard "Tony" Nichols''' (born 29 March 1938) is a retired [[Australian]] [[Anglican]] [[bishop]].<ref>[[Who's Who]] 2008: London, [[A & C Black]], 2008 {{ISBN|978-0-7136-8555-8}}</ref>

Nichols holds academic qualifications from the [[University|Universities]] of [[University of Sydney|Sydney]], [[University of London|London]], [[University of Sheffield|Sheffield]] and [[Macquarie University]]. He was a [[Latin]] and [[history]] [[teacher]] until his [[ordination]] to the [[priesthood]] in 1963.<ref>[[Crockford's Clerical Directory|Crockford’s 1975-76]] Lambeth, Church House, 1975 {{ISBN|0-19-200008-X}}</ref> He had [[Curate|curacies]] at St Paul’s [[Chatswood]] and St Bede’s [[Drummoyne]]. He was a [[lecturer]] in [[Biblical Studies]] at [[Moore College|Moore College, Sydney]] from 1968 to 1981 and [[Dean (education)|Dean]] of the [[Faculty (division)|Faculty]] of [[Theology]] at [[Satya Wacana Christian University]] until 1987. A further academic appointment at St Andrew’s Hall, [[Melbourne]] (a [[Church Mission Society]] training college) was followed by his ordination to the [[episcopate]] as the fifth [[Anglican Diocese of North West Australia|Bishop of North West Australia]],<ref>[http://www.anglicandnwa.org/history/ Diocesan website] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101126112406/http://www.anglicandnwa.org/history/ |date=2010-11-26 }}</ref> a position he held until 2003.  Since then he has been [[Dean (education)|Dean]] of Students and a [[lecturer]] in [[Biblical Studies]] at  Trinity Theological College in [[Perth, Western Australia|Perth]]. He is married to Judith M. Nichols.<ref>[http://justus.anglican.org/resources/misc/angcommuniondirectory.html Anglican Communion Directory, March 2000]</ref>

